	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">slobu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">@cpow: As a side, when I select NROM Hello World Project as a template should there be something added to the new project?  Any code or whatever?</div>
<br />Not yet, that's a WIP.  I'm investigating the best way to embed the project wizard material in the package.  Embedding them as resources could get unwieldy quickly.  Including them in a subfolder of the users installation might be nice, but runs the risk of the user modifying the example beyond usefulness which would render the IDE's capabilities to "help" that user useless on future projects.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>slobu</b> [ Tue May 01, 2012 12:08 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">cpow wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">slobu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">@cpow: As a side, when I select NROM Hello World Project as a template should there be something added to the new project?  Any code or whatever?</div><br />Not yet, that's a WIP.  I'm investigating the best way to embed the project wizard material in the package.  Embedding them as resources could get unwieldy quickly.  Including them in a subfolder of the users installation might be nice, but runs the risk of the user modifying the example beyond usefulness which would render the IDE's capabilities to "help" that user useless on future projects.</div>
<br />
<br />I'd suggest including the templates as renamed .zip files, say, nromhw.ntm.  Every time a template is needed the contents would be uncompressed.
<br />
<br />The user would have to intentionally open the base template file to monkey around.  I believe this is a good compromise between embedding and raw files as the ".ntm" templates can be easily updated.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


